@{
    this.ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}
<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>Guacamole MVC</h1>
    <p class="lead">Guacamole MVC is a POC of an ASP.NET MVC front-end for the <a href="http://guac-dev.org/" target="_blank">Guacamole</a> project, using <a href="http://signalr.net/" target="_blank">SignalR</a> as the communication layer.</p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">Installation/Configuration</div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <p>First, install a Guacamole server. See <a href="http://guac-dev.org/doc/gug/installing-guacamole.html" target="_blank">the doc</a>. (only the guacamole-server is needed).</p>
                <p>In the <var>web.config</var>, set the <var>GuacD:*</var> parameters to the GuacD server :</p>
                <samp>
                    &lt;add key="GuacD:Host" value="192.168.1.12" /&gt;<br />
                    &lt;add key="GuacD:Port" value="4822" /&gt;
                </samp>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">Usage</div>
            <div class="panel-body">
                <p>The servers available are hard-coded in the <var>GuacClient.cs</var> file.</p>
                <p class="text-muted">See the <var>Connect</var> methods.</p>
                <p>Go to the <a href="@Url.Action("Guacamole", "Home")">Guacamole</a> page for testing</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="panel panel-warning">
            <div class="panel-heading">Warning</div>
            <div class="panel-body"><p>It is only a proof-of-concept, not a ready-for-production code. <strong>USE AT YOUR OWN RISKS !!!</strong></p></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">TODO</div>
            <div class="panel-body"><p>Lots of things in this POC... (support for audio, clipboard, better error management...)</p></div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

